(1) A will or any part of it may be revoked by— (a) a later will or codicil duly executed and expressed to revoke the earlier will ; (b) a written declaration of intention to revoke, executed in the same manner as a will ; (c) burning, tearing or otherwise destroying the will by the testator or someone in his presence and by his direction with the intention of revoking it.
