Where any person dies leaving property, a court may appoint such person as the court thinks fit to be a receiver of the property pending a grant of probate or letters of administration if it appears on the application of any person—
(a) claiming to be interested in that property; or
claiming to be interested in that property; or
(b) having the custody or control of it at the time of the death of the testator ;
