On application in the prescribed manner, by an interested person, a court shall have jurisdiction in relation to a deceased person's estate —
(a) to decide whether a document purporting to be a will is a valid will and whether or not the deceased person died testate;
to decide whether a document purporting to be a will is a valid will and whether or not the deceased person died testate;
(b) to decide what is the property to which a deceased person was entitled at the date of his death;
to decide what is the property to which a deceased person was entitled at the date of his death;
(c) to order the sale or other disposition of property belonging to a deceased person's estate for the purpose of paying the debts of the deceased or for the purposes of distribution;
